I pushed some commits to ssh remote and then exited the SourceTree. A few minutes after I noticed two hg_local processes burning my CPUs. Killed them. Cannot easily reproduce again.

{code:shell}
/usr/bin/python /Applications/SourceTree.app/Contents/Resources/mercurial_local/hg_local heads -y --template {branch}\011\011{rev}:{node|short}\012
/usr/bin/python /Applications/SourceTree.app/Contents/Resources/mercurial_local/hg_local tags -y{code}

{{git commit --fixup}}

{{git commit --squash}}

[https://robots.thoughtbot.com/autosquashing-git-commits]

 

These would be very useful in the "Commit Options" drop-down.

Due to a tiny mistake in `stgpg.sh`, GPG can sometimes fail to sign commits, such as when rebasing with `commit.gpgsign` enabled. I'm only marking this as a high priority because it's super easy to fix. Instead of:
{code:java}
gpg2 --batch --no-tty $@{code}
it should be
{code:java}
gpg2 --batch --no-tty "$@"{code}
That's it, no more issues. Like [this StackExchange answer|http://unix.stackexchange.com/a/233774] mentions, `$@` should basically always be quoted.
